<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b50a07f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s628"><num value="628">§ 628.</num><heading> Expenditure for dredging within harbor lines</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No money appropriated for the improvement of rivers and harbors shall be expended for dredging inside of harbor lines duly established.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b50a080-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1892-07-13/ch158/s5">July 13, 1892, ch. 158, § 5</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/27/111">27 Stat. 111</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6b50a081-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6b50a082-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id6b50a083-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section is from the Rivers and Harbors Appropriation Act of 1892.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
